Roster vs Non-roster Players
  • All players on the NHL Roster have their cap hit count towards the team's cap hit.
  • Players who are not on the NHL Roster (in other leagues) do not count against the cap up to the burying threshold. Non-roster players who have a cap hit above the burying threshold carry a cap charge for the excess.
  • The team's cap hit each day includes players who are on the NHL Roster as of 5pm Eastern.
  • Players assigned to the minors must clear waivers if they are not waivers exempt.
  • See the PuckPedia Waivers Tracker here.

Capology
Search Capology Ask a Question
Contract Values By
Cap Hit
Average guaranteed compensation per year. Total amount paid on the contract (including salary & signing bonuses) divided by the # of contract years.
AAV - Average Annual Value
Total salary + signing bonuses + potential performance bonuses all divided by # of contract years.
Salary
The actual amount of compensation (salary & signing bonus) paid to a player in a specific season.
Signing Bonus
The signing bonus paid to a player in a specific season. This assumes the total signing bonus is paid by the current team.
Movement Clauses
No Movement Clause
Player cannot be traded, sent to minors or waived without player approval
No Trade Clause
Player cannot be traded without player approval
Modified No Trade Clause
Negotiated terms for potential trade. IE) List of acceptable trade teams
Contract Tags
Entry Level Contract
A player's first contract (if signed prior to age 25) is is constrained in salary and bonuses, and the term is based on their signing age.
More
Slide Eligible Contract
Players ELC may "slide" to a future season (the current season does not use up a year on the contract) if they play less than 10 NHL games.
More
+35
35+ Contract
Players signing a contact over age 35 that meet certain criteria have consequences to the team in the case of a buyout or being sent to minors.
More
Two-Way Contract
A contract where the player makes a lower amount when in the minors compared to being in NHL.
Waivers Exempt
Player is exempt from waivers and does not need to clear waivers to be assigned to the minors.
Offer Sheet Ineligible
Player is ineligible to sign an offer sheet from another team while a Restricted Free Agent
Slide Eligible Excluded From 50 Contract Limit
Slide eligible player who has been assigned to Junior, so they do not count against the 50 contract limit.
